      <guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.npr.org/2025/07/23/g-s1-78877/up-first-newsletter-jeffrey-epstein-obama-administration-russia-columbia-university-student-protestors</guid>
      <pubDate>Wed, 23 Jul 2025 11:04:08 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;div id="storytext" class="storytext storylocation linkLocation"&gt;       &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Good morning. You're reading the Up First newsletter. &lt;/em&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/newsletter/news" target="_blank"&gt;Subscribe&lt;/a&gt;&lt;em&gt; here to get it delivered to your inbox, and &lt;/em&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/podcasts/510318/up-first/" target="_blank"&gt;listen&lt;/a&gt;&lt;em&gt; to the Up First podcast for all the news you need to start your day.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;h3 class="edTag"&gt;Today's top stories&lt;/h3&gt;   &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;House Speaker Mike Johnson is sending lawmakers home today for an early start to their annual August recess. &lt;/strong&gt;He aims to avoid dragging out a fight among Republicans over releasing details of federal investigations into Jeffrey Epstein. President Trump, who was once friends with Epstein, faces backlash from supporters who are demanding more information. He has characterized the uproar as a &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/07/22/nx-s1-5476234/trump-epstein-obama" target="_blank"&gt;politically motivated "witch hunt"&lt;/a&gt; that distracts from his agenda. Republicans hope the controversy will subside while they're away, but some believe that won't be the case.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div id="resg-s1-62524" class="bucketwrap image large"&gt;             &lt;div     class="imagewrap has-source-dimensions"     data-crop-type=""     style="         --source-width: 8050;         --source-height: 4528;     " &gt;         &lt;picture&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/8050x4528+0+839/resize/400/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F6b%2F90%2Fc583f427404181fc2e726dbc5b7d%2Fgettyimages-2210759447.jpg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/8050x4528+0+839/resize/600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F6b%2F90%2Fc583f427404181fc2e726dbc5b7d%2Fgettyimages-2210759447.jpg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/8050x4528+0+839/resize/800/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F6b%2F90%2Fc583f427404181fc2e726dbc5b7d%2Fgettyimages-2210759447.jpg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/8050x4528+0+839/resize/900/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F6b%2F90%2Fc583f427404181fc2e726dbc5b7d%2Fgettyimages-2210759447.jpg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/8050x4528+0+839/resize/1200/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F6b%2F90%2Fc583f427404181fc2e726dbc5b7d%2Fgettyimages-2210759447.jpg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/8050x4528+0+839/resize/1600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F6b%2F90%2Fc583f427404181fc2e726dbc5b7d%2Fgettyimages-2210759447.jpg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/8050x4528+0+839/resize/1800/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F6b%2F90%2Fc583f427404181fc2e726dbc5b7d%2Fgettyimages-2210759447.jpg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/8050x4528+0+839/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F6b%2F90%2Fc583f427404181fc2e726dbc5b7d%2Fgettyimages-2210759447.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1025px) 650px, calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/webp" /&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/8050x4528+0+839/resize/400/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F6b%2F90%2Fc583f427404181fc2e726dbc5b7d%2Fgettyimages-2210759447.jpg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/8050x4528+0+839/resize/600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F6b%2F90%2Fc583f427404181fc2e726dbc5b7d%2Fgettyimages-2210759447.jpg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/8050x4528+0+839/resize/800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F6b%2F90%2Fc583f427404181fc2e726dbc5b7d%2Fgettyimages-2210759447.jpg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/8050x4528+0+839/resize/900/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F6b%2F90%2Fc583f427404181fc2e726dbc5b7d%2Fgettyimages-2210759447.jpg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/8050x4528+0+839/resize/1200/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F6b%2F90%2Fc583f427404181fc2e726dbc5b7d%2Fgettyimages-2210759447.jpg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/8050x4528+0+839/resize/1600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F6b%2F90%2Fc583f427404181fc2e726dbc5b7d%2Fgettyimages-2210759447.jpg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/8050x4528+0+839/resize/1800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F6b%2F90%2Fc583f427404181fc2e726dbc5b7d%2Fgettyimages-2210759447.jpg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/8050x4528+0+839/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F6b%2F90%2Fc583f427404181fc2e726dbc5b7d%2Fgettyimages-2210759447.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1025px) 650px, calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/jpeg" /&gt;             &lt;img src="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/8050x4528+0+839/resize/1100/quality/50/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F6b%2F90%2Fc583f427404181fc2e726dbc5b7d%2Fgettyimages-2210759447.jpg" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/8050x4528+0+839/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F6b%2F90%2Fc583f427404181fc2e726dbc5b7d%2Fgettyimages-2210759447.jpg" class="img" alt="The U.S. Capitol on April 21, 2025. Democratic lawmakers are asking the National Labor Relations Board to respond to a recent whistleblower disclosure that documents concerns that officials with the Department of Government Efficiency team may have taken sensitive information about workers." loading="lazy" /&gt;         &lt;/picture&gt; &lt;/div&gt; &lt;div class="credit-caption"&gt;     &lt;div class="caption-wrap"&gt;         &lt;div class="caption" aria-label="Image caption"&gt;             &lt;p&gt;                 The U.S. Capitol on April 21, 2025. Democratic lawmakers are asking the National Labor Relations Board to respond to a recent whistleblower disclosure that documents concerns that officials with the Department of Government Efficiency team may have taken sensitive information about workers.                 &lt;b class="credit" aria-label="Image credit"&gt;                                          Brendan Smialowski/AFP via Getty Images                                      &lt;/b&gt;                 &lt;b class="hide-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;             &lt;/p&gt;         &lt;/div&gt;               &lt;b class="toggle-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;     &lt;/div&gt;       &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;ul class="edTag"&gt;&lt;li&gt;🎧 &lt;strong&gt;"It is pretty rare to see the House floor paralyzed like this, even for a day,"&lt;/strong&gt; NPR's Claudia Grisales tells &lt;em&gt;Up First&lt;/em&gt;. The extended recess leaves House Republicans with tight deadlines for critical legislation once they return in September. Trump has said related grand jury files will be released, but some Republican voters say they want the administration to do more. Rep. Thomas Massie, R-Ky., is leading a bipartisan petition that could force a vote to release the Epstein records. Massie says he believes Americans want to see justice and transparency, and, when they return in September, it &lt;a href="https://one.npr.org/?sharedMediaId=1256100345:x" target="_blank"&gt;will become a problem for&lt;/a&gt; Johnson and Trump.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;       &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Trump deflected questions yesterday about the Epstein case, shifting the focus to an old controversy&lt;/strong&gt;: Russian interference in the 2016 U.S. presidential election. This comes after Director of National Intelligence Tulsi Gabbard stated last week that she released evidence that former President Barack Obama and his national security officials &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/07/21/nx-s1-5475171/trump-gabbard-russia-2016-election" target="_blank"&gt;manipulated intelligence to target Trump&lt;/a&gt;. The documents released include nearly 100 pages of newly declassified Obama-era emails, leading up to and after the 2016 election. &lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;ul class="edTag"&gt;&lt;li&gt;🎧&lt;strong&gt; Many of the emails focused on whether Russian hackers had or could successfully hack the election&lt;/strong&gt;, says NPR's Jenna McLaughlin, who read through the documents. The Obama administration's national security officials said it was unlikely Russian hackers could breach election infrastructure on a large scale without detection. After Trump won the 2016 election, Obama asked intelligence officials to write an assessment on everything they knew about Russian interference in the election cycle. The report never stated that Russia hacked the election, but did state that Russia &lt;a href="https://one.npr.org/?sharedMediaId=1256100345:x" target="_blank"&gt;attempted to influence the election&lt;/a&gt; using tactics such as disinformation on social media and bot farms.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;   &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Over 70 Columbia University students are being disciplined for participating in a pro-Palestinian protest at the university's Butler Library in May.&lt;/strong&gt; The disciplinary actions include probation, suspensions, expulsions and degree revocations. More than two-thirds of the students were suspended or expelled. The move comes as university officials continue to negotiate a deal with the Trump administration to release frozen research funding. They say the frozen funds &lt;a href="https://gothamist.com/news/columbia-disciplines-70-students-for-protest-as-school-pleads-with-trump-for-funding" target="_blank"&gt;amount to about $1 billion in grants&lt;/a&gt;. &lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;       &lt;ul class="edTag"&gt;&lt;li&gt;🎧 &lt;strong&gt;The disciplinary actions are significant because the Trump administration is paying attention to how universities handle protests&lt;/strong&gt; as part of their efforts to combat antisemitism on campus, says Jessica Gould of NPR network station WNYC. Columbia's Acting President Claire Shipman states that the university is working to make improvements to the campus climate, and the fact that they are facing pressure from the government &lt;a href="https://one.npr.org/?sharedMediaId=1256100345:1269684193" target="_blank"&gt;doesn't make the university's problems less real&lt;/a&gt;. Many Jewish and Muslim students at the university have said they have faced harassment since the Oct. 7, 2023, Hamas attacks on Israel.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;   &lt;h3 class="edTag"&gt;Life advice&lt;/h3&gt;   &lt;div id="resg-s1-78056" class="bucketwrap image large"&gt;             &lt;div     class="imagewrap has-source-dimensions"     data-crop-type=""     style="         --source-width: 4961;         --source-height: 2791;     " &gt;         &lt;picture&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4961x2791+0+342/resize/400/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fd8%2Ff7%2F582ffd4a475181228b140aabed7b%2Flk-should-i-buy-this-gettyimages-1477195126.jpg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4961x2791+0+342/resize/600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fd8%2Ff7%2F582ffd4a475181228b140aabed7b%2Flk-should-i-buy-this-gettyimages-1477195126.jpg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4961x2791+0+342/resize/800/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fd8%2Ff7%2F582ffd4a475181228b140aabed7b%2Flk-should-i-buy-this-gettyimages-1477195126.jpg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4961x2791+0+342/resize/900/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fd8%2Ff7%2F582ffd4a475181228b140aabed7b%2Flk-should-i-buy-this-gettyimages-1477195126.jpg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4961x2791+0+342/resize/1200/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fd8%2Ff7%2F582ffd4a475181228b140aabed7b%2Flk-should-i-buy-this-gettyimages-1477195126.jpg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4961x2791+0+342/resize/1600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fd8%2Ff7%2F582ffd4a475181228b140aabed7b%2Flk-should-i-buy-this-gettyimages-1477195126.jpg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4961x2791+0+342/resize/1800/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fd8%2Ff7%2F582ffd4a475181228b140aabed7b%2Flk-should-i-buy-this-gettyimages-1477195126.jpg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4961x2791+0+342/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fd8%2Ff7%2F582ffd4a475181228b140aabed7b%2Flk-should-i-buy-this-gettyimages-1477195126.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1025px) 650px, calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/webp" /&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4961x2791+0+342/resize/400/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fd8%2Ff7%2F582ffd4a475181228b140aabed7b%2Flk-should-i-buy-this-gettyimages-1477195126.jpg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4961x2791+0+342/resize/600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fd8%2Ff7%2F582ffd4a475181228b140aabed7b%2Flk-should-i-buy-this-gettyimages-1477195126.jpg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4961x2791+0+342/resize/800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fd8%2Ff7%2F582ffd4a475181228b140aabed7b%2Flk-should-i-buy-this-gettyimages-1477195126.jpg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4961x2791+0+342/resize/900/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fd8%2Ff7%2F582ffd4a475181228b140aabed7b%2Flk-should-i-buy-this-gettyimages-1477195126.jpg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4961x2791+0+342/resize/1200/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fd8%2Ff7%2F582ffd4a475181228b140aabed7b%2Flk-should-i-buy-this-gettyimages-1477195126.jpg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4961x2791+0+342/resize/1600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fd8%2Ff7%2F582ffd4a475181228b140aabed7b%2Flk-should-i-buy-this-gettyimages-1477195126.jpg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4961x2791+0+342/resize/1800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fd8%2Ff7%2F582ffd4a475181228b140aabed7b%2Flk-should-i-buy-this-gettyimages-1477195126.jpg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4961x2791+0+342/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fd8%2Ff7%2F582ffd4a475181228b140aabed7b%2Flk-should-i-buy-this-gettyimages-1477195126.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1025px) 650px, calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/jpeg" /&gt;             &lt;img src="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4961x2791+0+342/resize/1100/quality/50/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fd8%2Ff7%2F582ffd4a475181228b140aabed7b%2Flk-should-i-buy-this-gettyimages-1477195126.jpg" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4961x2791+0+342/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fd8%2Ff7%2F582ffd4a475181228b140aabed7b%2Flk-should-i-buy-this-gettyimages-1477195126.jpg" class="img" alt="A photo collage showing a pair of outstretched arms donning pink sleeves. The person holds a phone out in front of a pair of lime-colored sneakers. The lime sneakers are in the center of a line up of identical sneakers in varying bright colors. The image is set against a gradient background that changes from aqua to purple. " loading="lazy" /&gt;         &lt;/picture&gt; &lt;/div&gt; &lt;div class="credit-caption"&gt;     &lt;div class="caption-wrap"&gt;         &lt;div class="caption" aria-label="Image caption"&gt;             &lt;p&gt;                 shopping for sneakers on the internet                 &lt;b class="credit" aria-label="Image credit"&gt;                                          We Are/Getty Images                                      &lt;/b&gt;                 &lt;b class="hide-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;             &lt;/p&gt;         &lt;/div&gt;               &lt;b class="toggle-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;     &lt;/div&gt;       &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Buying only what you need instead of what you want can be a hard rule to follow. It's OK to indulge in what you desire now and then, but the key is to be intentional. If you are unsure whether to swipe that card or walk away, this &lt;em&gt;Life Kit &lt;/em&gt;guide can &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/07/19/nx-s1-5471414/money-shopping-budget-mindful-purchases" target="_blank"&gt;help you make a mindful decision&lt;/a&gt; you won't regret. &lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;ul class="edTag"&gt;&lt;li&gt;💳 Hold off on spending if you have to pull funds you set aside for basic needs. Don't take money from your emergency fund or money saved for vacations.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;💳 When feeling spendy, use the acronym HALT to check in on yourself. Are you hungry, angry, lonely or tired? If so, there could be another way to fill your need.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;💳 Before buying, shop around for the best price and read reviews to make sure you're getting the best bang for your buck.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;💳 If you are buying the latest and greatest in an attempt to achieve status, consider why that item matters so much to your self-esteem.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;   &lt;p&gt;For more guidance on shopping mindfully, &lt;a href="https://one.npr.org/?sharedMediaId=nx-s1-5471414:g-s1-78189" target="_blank"&gt;listen to this episode of NPR's &lt;em&gt;Life Kit&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;. Subscribe to &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/newsletter/life-kit" target="_blank"&gt;the&lt;em&gt; Life Kit&lt;/em&gt; newsletter&lt;/a&gt; for expert advice on love, money, relationships and more.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Life Kit&lt;/em&gt; is &lt;a href="https://www.instagram.com/nprlifekit/#" target="_blank"&gt;now on Instagram&lt;/a&gt;. Follow the page for bite-size versions of its episodes on money, health, relationships and more. Recent posts include a reel on how to properly spray mosquito repellent, a comic on how to intervene when someone is harassed or attacked, and feel-good exercises for sore, achy feet. Look out for opportunities to &lt;a href="https://www.instagram.com/nprlifekit/#" target="_blank"&gt;share your own advice&lt;/a&gt; with the&lt;em&gt; Life Kit &lt;/em&gt;audience too.&lt;/p&gt;       &lt;h3 class="edTag"&gt;Picture show&lt;/h3&gt;   &lt;div id="resg-s1-77870" class="bucketwrap image large"&gt;             &lt;div     class="imagewrap has-source-dimensions"     data-crop-type=""     style="         --source-width: 7725;         --source-height: 4343;     " &gt;         &lt;picture&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/7725x4343+911+1229/resize/400/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F5b%2F6c%2Fcc77f4f94f30b3d26539786c07e9%2F20250625-franklloydwrighthouse-kc-31.jpg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/7725x4343+911+1229/resize/600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F5b%2F6c%2Fcc77f4f94f30b3d26539786c07e9%2F20250625-franklloydwrighthouse-kc-31.jpg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/7725x4343+911+1229/resize/800/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F5b%2F6c%2Fcc77f4f94f30b3d26539786c07e9%2F20250625-franklloydwrighthouse-kc-31.jpg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/7725x4343+911+1229/resize/900/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F5b%2F6c%2Fcc77f4f94f30b3d26539786c07e9%2F20250625-franklloydwrighthouse-kc-31.jpg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/7725x4343+911+1229/resize/1200/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F5b%2F6c%2Fcc77f4f94f30b3d26539786c07e9%2F20250625-franklloydwrighthouse-kc-31.jpg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/7725x4343+911+1229/resize/1600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F5b%2F6c%2Fcc77f4f94f30b3d26539786c07e9%2F20250625-franklloydwrighthouse-kc-31.jpg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/7725x4343+911+1229/resize/1800/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F5b%2F6c%2Fcc77f4f94f30b3d26539786c07e9%2F20250625-franklloydwrighthouse-kc-31.jpg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/7725x4343+911+1229/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F5b%2F6c%2Fcc77f4f94f30b3d26539786c07e9%2F20250625-franklloydwrighthouse-kc-31.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1025px) 650px, calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/webp" /&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/7725x4343+911+1229/resize/400/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F5b%2F6c%2Fcc77f4f94f30b3d26539786c07e9%2F20250625-franklloydwrighthouse-kc-31.jpg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/7725x4343+911+1229/resize/600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F5b%2F6c%2Fcc77f4f94f30b3d26539786c07e9%2F20250625-franklloydwrighthouse-kc-31.jpg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/7725x4343+911+1229/resize/800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F5b%2F6c%2Fcc77f4f94f30b3d26539786c07e9%2F20250625-franklloydwrighthouse-kc-31.jpg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/7725x4343+911+1229/resize/900/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F5b%2F6c%2Fcc77f4f94f30b3d26539786c07e9%2F20250625-franklloydwrighthouse-kc-31.jpg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/7725x4343+911+1229/resize/1200/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F5b%2F6c%2Fcc77f4f94f30b3d26539786c07e9%2F20250625-franklloydwrighthouse-kc-31.jpg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/7725x4343+911+1229/resize/1600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F5b%2F6c%2Fcc77f4f94f30b3d26539786c07e9%2F20250625-franklloydwrighthouse-kc-31.jpg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/7725x4343+911+1229/resize/1800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F5b%2F6c%2Fcc77f4f94f30b3d26539786c07e9%2F20250625-franklloydwrighthouse-kc-31.jpg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/7725x4343+911+1229/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F5b%2F6c%2Fcc77f4f94f30b3d26539786c07e9%2F20250625-franklloydwrighthouse-kc-31.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1025px) 650px, calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/jpeg" /&gt;             &lt;img src="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/7725x4343+911+1229/resize/1100/quality/50/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F5b%2F6c%2Fcc77f4f94f30b3d26539786c07e9%2F20250625-franklloydwrighthouse-kc-31.jpg" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/7725x4343+911+1229/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F5b%2F6c%2Fcc77f4f94f30b3d26539786c07e9%2F20250625-franklloydwrighthouse-kc-31.jpg" class="img" alt="The Reisley House was designed by Frank Lloyd Wright in the 1950s. Roland Reaisley, the original owner of the house, still resides there 70 years later." loading="lazy" /&gt;         &lt;/picture&gt; &lt;/div&gt; &lt;div class="credit-caption"&gt;     &lt;div class="caption-wrap"&gt;         &lt;div class="caption" aria-label="Image caption"&gt;             &lt;p&gt;                 The Reisley House was designed by Frank Lloyd Wright in the 1950s. Roland Reaisley, the original owner of the house, still resides there 70 years later.                 &lt;b class="credit" aria-label="Image credit"&gt;                                          Keren Carrión/NPR                                      &lt;/b&gt;                 &lt;b class="hide-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;             &lt;/p&gt;         &lt;/div&gt;               &lt;b class="toggle-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;     &lt;/div&gt;       &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Roland Reisley turned 101 earlier this year. While his remarkable health is noteworthy, he likes to brag about something else. He takes pride in the fact that he is still living in the home famed architect Frank Lloyd Wright designed for him. For 73 years, Reisley has lived in this house, which is nestled in the woods of Westchester County, N.Y. It's one of 47 that make up the mid-century modern village of Usonia. Wright envisioned Usonia as a place to create beautiful, affordable homes connected to nature for middle-class Americans. The house is constructed with local materials and features a flat roof, a carport, wood paneling, built-in shelving, concrete floors and custom furniture. &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/07/23/nx-s1-5468949/frank-lloyd-wright-usonia-house" target="_blank"&gt;Take a look inside the house&lt;/a&gt;, which is now listed on the National Register of Historic Places.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;h3 class="edTag"&gt;3 things to know before you go&lt;/h3&gt;   &lt;div id="resg-s1-78754" class="bucketwrap image large"&gt;             &lt;div     class="imagewrap has-source-dimensions"     data-crop-type=""     style="         --source-width: 2000;         --source-height: 1125;     " &gt;         &lt;picture&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2000x1125+0+308/resize/400/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Ff8%2Fd8%2F273e4be849f88b5ed557272af838%2Fgettyimages-2252573.jpg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2000x1125+0+308/resize/600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Ff8%2Fd8%2F273e4be849f88b5ed557272af838%2Fgettyimages-2252573.jpg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2000x1125+0+308/resize/800/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Ff8%2Fd8%2F273e4be849f88b5ed557272af838%2Fgettyimages-2252573.jpg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2000x1125+0+308/resize/900/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Ff8%2Fd8%2F273e4be849f88b5ed557272af838%2Fgettyimages-2252573.jpg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2000x1125+0+308/resize/1200/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Ff8%2Fd8%2F273e4be849f88b5ed557272af838%2Fgettyimages-2252573.jpg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2000x1125+0+308/resize/1600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Ff8%2Fd8%2F273e4be849f88b5ed557272af838%2Fgettyimages-2252573.jpg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2000x1125+0+308/resize/1800/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Ff8%2Fd8%2F273e4be849f88b5ed557272af838%2Fgettyimages-2252573.jpg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2000x1125+0+308/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Ff8%2Fd8%2F273e4be849f88b5ed557272af838%2Fgettyimages-2252573.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1025px) 650px, calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/webp" /&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2000x1125+0+308/resize/400/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Ff8%2Fd8%2F273e4be849f88b5ed557272af838%2Fgettyimages-2252573.jpg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2000x1125+0+308/resize/600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Ff8%2Fd8%2F273e4be849f88b5ed557272af838%2Fgettyimages-2252573.jpg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2000x1125+0+308/resize/800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Ff8%2Fd8%2F273e4be849f88b5ed557272af838%2Fgettyimages-2252573.jpg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2000x1125+0+308/resize/900/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Ff8%2Fd8%2F273e4be849f88b5ed557272af838%2Fgettyimages-2252573.jpg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2000x1125+0+308/resize/1200/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Ff8%2Fd8%2F273e4be849f88b5ed557272af838%2Fgettyimages-2252573.jpg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2000x1125+0+308/resize/1600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Ff8%2Fd8%2F273e4be849f88b5ed557272af838%2Fgettyimages-2252573.jpg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2000x1125+0+308/resize/1800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Ff8%2Fd8%2F273e4be849f88b5ed557272af838%2Fgettyimages-2252573.jpg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2000x1125+0+308/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Ff8%2Fd8%2F273e4be849f88b5ed557272af838%2Fgettyimages-2252573.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1025px) 650px, calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/jpeg" /&gt;             &lt;img src="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2000x1125+0+308/resize/1100/quality/50/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Ff8%2Fd8%2F273e4be849f88b5ed557272af838%2Fgettyimages-2252573.jpg" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2000x1125+0+308/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Ff8%2Fd8%2F273e4be849f88b5ed557272af838%2Fgettyimages-2252573.jpg" class="img" alt="Ozzy Osbourne at &amp;quot;The Tonight Show with Jay Leno&amp;quot; at the NBC Studios in Los Angeles, Ca. October 12, 2001. Photo by Kevin Winter/Getty Images." loading="lazy" /&gt;         &lt;/picture&gt; &lt;/div&gt; &lt;div class="credit-caption"&gt;     &lt;div class="caption-wrap"&gt;         &lt;div class="caption" aria-label="Image caption"&gt;             &lt;p&gt;                 Ozzy Osbourne at "The Tonight Show with Jay Leno" at the NBC Studios in Los Angeles, Ca. October 12, 2001. Photo by Kevin Winter/Getty Images.                 &lt;b class="credit" aria-label="Image credit"&gt;                                          Kevin Winter/Getty Images/Getty Images North America                                      &lt;/b&gt;                 &lt;b class="hide-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;             &lt;/p&gt;         &lt;/div&gt;               &lt;b class="toggle-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;     &lt;/div&gt;       &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;ol class="edTag"&gt;&lt;li&gt;Heavy metal icon Ozzy Osbourne, known as the "Prince of Darkness " and the lead singer of Black Sabbath, has &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/07/22/833512508/ozzy-osbourne-black-sabbath-obituary" target="_blank"&gt;died at the age of 76&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Coca-Cola announced yesterday that it would expand its product line by introducing a Coke &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/07/22/nx-s1-5476161/coca-cola-cane-sugar-coke-trump-recipe" target="_blank"&gt;sweetened with U.S. cane sugar&lt;/a&gt; this fall.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;A new study from Harvard University researchers analyzed the birthing records of 58,007 women and found that larger families tend to have &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/07/22/nx-s1-5471382/births-boys-girls-odd-chance-research" target="_blank"&gt;either all girls or all boys&lt;/a&gt;, rather than a mixture of both.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ol&gt;   &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;This newsletter was edited by &lt;/em&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/people/859721331/suzanne-nuyen"target="_blank"   &gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Suzanne Nuyen&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/div&gt;</description>
